President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has authorized additional disaster assistance for the State of New Mexico. The increase in Federal funding is for Public Assistance projects related to wildfires, straight-line winds, flooding, mudflows, and debris flows that occurred between April 5 and July 23, 2022. The President's order increases Federal funds for Public Assistance to cover 100 percent of the total eligible costs for projects responding to the Cerro Pelado Fire in Los Alamos and Sandoval Counties. For further information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.